name: Irwin
description:
In Murfreeseboro-Irwin is a young Australian Shepherd mix who will quickly work his way into your heart. We don’t know what the mix is, but his foster parents guess he has a little Pyrenees in him based on his paw gestures, herding style and eyes. 

He’s about 3 years old (though could be younger, the vet could give a better estimate if Irwin would let them look at his teeth), and 54 lbs. 

Irwin’s origins are unknown, then he spent several months at a rural shelter and was up for euthanasia when ASF stepped in and saved his life! He is very timid at first and took several weeks at his foster home to relax and start to show his personality. This is a recurring theme with him, he needs time and space to adjust to new people, places and things. Slow introductions to people and dogs will help Irwin to be successful in the long run. He also does best with some initial boundaries, stick to the butt scratches until he knows you please!

Irwin is a medium energy dog, he needs daily exercise but he’s not an overachiever. A few 15 minute play sessions or a couple miles on a walk and he’ll be good to go. Irwin’s like his foster dad, you better get all the walking in you want to do because once he gets back to the car he’s ready to go home and take a nap. 

Tennis balls produce much prancing around in excitement for you to throw them in the backyard; he loves a good game of fetch. Irwin can get over excited during backyard playtimes; this is manifested in jumping and nipping (at the same time). And let me tell you this boy can JUMP. A nip on your head is easy peasy for him! He’s working on more appropriate behaviors at his foster home, but will need continued training. It’s for this reason that children should be at least 12 years old. I know he won’t bite but even at a sturdy 33 years old it’s intimidating to see him run full speed across the yard and then jump! A fenced yard would be great but must be 6 feet, a 4 foot fence won’t hold this boy.

Irwin’s most defining characteristic is that he’s a big ol’ love bug. He would like constant attention! If you’re not doing anything, you should be petting him. If you’re doing something, you should be petting him. He will use his paws to pull your hand to pets if not otherwise occupied or nudge you to remind you to keep rubbing his belly. He is never more than about 15 feet from his foster mom and loves to “go” if that means staying with his people. 

While he can stay home alone (in a crate or uncrated), he would do best if not left alone for too long daily. If you do leave him, he will need a commensurate amount of time devoted to loving on him when you return. Irwin would do fine as an only dog or with a canine companion, just keep in mind it will take him a while to warm up to his new dog pal.

Irwin is working on curbing his jumping, but you should jump at the chance to meet this charming fellow!

Currently fostered in Murfreesboro, TN. There is an additional $20 microchip fee which includes registration and transfer to his new furever family.

Here is the application: https://www.australianshepherdsfurever.org/adoption-application

name: Koda
description: Koda is a  3 year old little boxer shep about 40 lbs. Koda lives with his brother and while they get along most of the time,occasionally they get into a fight without a clear trigger, so after unsuccessfully trying to correct this issue with training the family has decided to let koda go on to another family. He does get along fine with the other resident dog but we are hoping for an only dog home for him. He is a stunning fluffy boy with a super sweet nature. He has been raised with boys and loves his kids! He loves all people! Loves family time weather it’s watching tv on the couch or exploring outside. He is house broken but may have some accidents when he moves until he acclimates. He’s great on leash. He crate trained. He’s over all well behaved in the house. He loves his yard time.  He’s really a great boy -he just don’t get along as well as we had hoped with other dogs. Who can help this handsome pup live his very best life moving forward!

name: Bucky
description:
FOSTER OR FOREVER HOME NEEDED
Say hello to this sweet boy, Bucky! He is a 4-year-old, 15 LB terrier mix who came to us from an overcrowded shelter in CA.

Bucky is an awesome little dog! He is smart, affectionate, loving, and a great little adventure buddy. He loves to cuddle up on his persons lap and watch the world go by. He would love a forever home that takes him on daily walks and lets him snuggle up on the couch with them at the end of the day. 

Bucky loves other dogs and would enjoy having another canine companion in the home as a playmate. He would also be fine as an only dog soaking up all the love and attention if he had continued socialization. Bucky is ready to find his forever home and be someone’s loyal and loving companion!

Bucky is UTD on vaccinations, microchipped, and neutered. His adoption fee is $500.

name: Matisse
description: Hi my name is Matisse and I'm a fun and energetic 5 month old pup.  Let's just say I love everyone and everything.  Here is a short list of the things I love: romping with my sister Monet, playing with my foster brother who is a big German Shepherd, licking crumbs off the floor, exploring everything in the backyard, going for car rides, napping and cuddling with my foster Mom.  I'm working on my potty training but do really well when my foster Mom takes me outside frequently.  Otherwise I use the potty pads and know that's where I'm supposed to pee if I have to go and no one takes me outside fast enough.  I've spent time in the crate when my foster Mom has to do people stuff, and I will let you know that I'm not a fan of it.  But I settle down and having a chewstick helps.  I'm very treat motivated.  It would be fun if I got adopted with my sister Monet, but it's not necessary since I bond well with all things (except I haven't met a cat yet so I'm not sure about kitties)

name: Sweet Caroline
description:
Sweet Caroline is an absolutely beautiful girl with a sweet temperament.  She is about 1 year and a half old and came to us pregnant.  We have her and one of her puppies remaining in rescue, the other puppies have all been adopted.

This girl is a perfect fit for anyone.  She loves people, loves being inside with you and is house trained and not destructive as long as she has toys or something to keep her busy. She's crate trained and great on a leash.  She's a very good girl.

Caroline would love to find her forever.  She is spayed and current on vaccinations and is microchipped.  Her adoption fee is $150.  Please call Lori at 405-620-2411 to set up a time to meet this wonderful girl!

name: Cucumber - Mild-Mannered, Trained
breed: German Shepherd Dog & American Staffordshire Terrier Mix
description:
Cucumber's greatest hits: https://tinyurl.com/yra99uu3

My heart fills with love with I think of Cucumber. I've been fostering him since Oct 2023, and have treated him as my own. He has made amazing strides during that time, and I know will only shine brighter with continued guidance and nurturing.

Cucumber is mild-mannered and has already had more foundational training under his belt than most dogs have in their lifetime.  He's about 80 lbs, 1.5 years old, and a beautiful mix of Siberian husky, German shepherd, American Staffie, pittie, and a touch of doberman. His age, size, and mix may lead you to think he's a handful but such is not a case at all. 

Some of his qualities:

* Housetrained

* Crate-trained. He LOVES his crate!

* Quiet. Not at all a nuisance barker, even when the little yappy dogs next door fence bark at him.

* Walks well on leash. 

* Rides calmly in the car.

* Great off-leash. While he hasn't been formally trained on recall, he is responsive when I call his name during our hikes.

* Highly food-motivated -- great for training1

* Tolerant with being handled by those he trusts. He doesn't mind having his nails dremeled, teeth brushed, or being given a bath. 

* A follower who wants to please. He just needs to understand what you're asking of him.

* Some commands that have been introduced: sit, down, stay, roll over, spin, wait, look, with me, leave it. Also trained to be comfortable with a gentle leader, soft cone of shame, and muzzle, to wait at the door before being released, and extended down-stays.

* Good with most dogs. (Note: he is very vocal when playing and makes growly and barky noises, which may be off-putting to some dogs--and humans--not familiar with this, but it is just his form of play.)

* More on the submissive side.  Easily corrected.

* Would be fine as an only dog or in a multi-dog household.

* Loves to fetch. He will bring the ball back.

* Loves water.

* Not high energy. 

* Mellow and well-behaved in the house.

* Affectionate but not needy.

* SUPER lovable!

Every single person who has spent quality time with Cucumber knows what a wonderful dog he is. His disposition is so good-natured. He is a devoted companion and the best side-kick. He'll make you laugh and fill your heart with immense joy, as he's done for me. It has been an honor to help this boy blossom, and I hope his new family appreciates him as much as I do, and as much as he deserves.

Watch Cucumber's complete playlist here:
https://tinyurl.com/2s39k33b

Adoption requirements:  minimum 24 years of age

name: Lydia Deetz
description:
This super lovable puppy came to Sammie's Friends as a found puppy, arriving with her litter mates. She was taken into foster care but has returned to Sammie's Friends as her potential adopter was no longer able to care for her. 
She is fun loving and very energetic and could use a bit of puppy training.
Her personality is delightful, she has a wiggle that won't stop, is full of kisses and is she's a busy little lady!

name: Panda
description:
Meet Panda, an energetic and playful 7-month-old female Cattle Dog mix with a heart full of love! Panda is always ready for fun, whether it’s splashing around in a kiddie pool, chasing toys, or running after balls. She has a lively spirit and would thrive in an active home where she can keep up with kids who love to play just as much as she does.

Panda is great with other dogs, but since she enjoys being the leader of the pack, a gradual introduction would be ideal—especially if paired with a more submissive dog. With her high energy and playful personality, Panda would make a fantastic companion for an active family looking to add some extra joy and excitement to their lives. If you’re ready for endless fun and affection, Panda is the one for you!

Panda is located in the Greater Los Angeles area.

Please visit our website to complete an adoption application: https://jasonheigl.foundation/adopt/panda/
